  "original_title": "Sri Lanka state run Rupavahini, ITN off air amid protests",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka state run Rupavahini, ITN off air amid protests",
      "author": "",
      "body_lines": [
        "ECONOMYNEXT \u2013 Sri Lanka\u2019s state-run Rupavahini went off air for a time after two protestors were interviewed live on air and suspended programs, while Independent Television Network another state broadcaster is also displaying colour bars.",
        "The headquarters of the Sri Lanka Rupahavini Corporation (SLRC), the state-owned television network, was given heavy security from morning with authorities expecting protestors expected lay siege to the station.",
        "Two spokesmen who said they represented \u2018Aragala Protestors\u2019 said they have taken over the station on behalf of the people and exhorted on the workers to be independent.",
        "\u201cWe have not even aimed a stone at Rupavahini,\u201d the representative said. \u201cWe only made a request",
        "to change the broadcast and  join the aragala and not to join any leader than comes but be independent.\u201d",
        "\u201cNow as aragala we took this over for the people we thank the staff for accepting us.",
        "Separately state-run Independent Television Network has also suspended normal programming as is displaying colour bars. (Colombo/Jul13/2022)"
      ],
